.SH NAME
hsh \- simple UNIX command interpreter

.SH DESCRIPTION
hsh is a simple shell that replicates the functionality of /bin/sh It reads commands from standard input then finds programs using the PATH variable, and executes them using fork and execve

.SH COMPILATION
gcc -Wall -Werror -Wextra -pedantic -std=gnu89 *.c -o hsh

